# Citadels Game

A Java implementation of the Citadels board game.

## Project Overview
This is a Java-based implementation of the Citadels board game, featuring a command-line interface and JSON-based game state management.

## Prerequisites
- Java 8 or higher
- Gradle 5.6.3 or higher

## Building the Project
To build the project, use one of the following commands:
```bash
./gradlew build
# or
gradle build
```

## Running the Game
To run the game:
```bash
./gradlew jar
# or
gradle jar 
java -jar build/libs/citadels.jar
```

## Documentation
### Javadoc
To generate and view the Javadoc documentation:
```bash
./gradlew clean javadoc
# or
gradle javadoc
start .\build\docs\javadoc\index.html
```

### Test Coverage Report
To generate and view the test coverage report:
```bash
gradle test jacocoTestReport
start .\build\reports\jacoco\test\html\index.html
```

## Project Structure
- `src/` - Source code directory
- `build/` - Build output directory
- `doc/` - Additional documentation
- `plantuml/` - UML diagrams
- `tools/` - Utility tools

## Dependencies
- JUnit Jupiter (5.8.2) - Testing framework
- Mockito (4.5.1) - Mocking framework
- JSON Simple (1.1.1) - JSON processing
- Gson (2.10.1) - JSON serialization/deserialization

## Build Artifacts
The build process creates:
- `build/libs/citadels.jar` - Executable JAR file
- `build/docs/javadoc/` - Javadoc documentation
- `build/reports/jacoco/` - Test coverage reports
